    "updated_at": "2013-04-23T05:13:56Z",
    "body": "Note that LLVM has [overflow intrinsics](http://llvm.org/docs/LangRef.html#arithmetic-with-overflow-intrinsics) which compiles to overflow flag and carry flag (if things are aligned). Mono compiles C# checked operators to LLVM overflow intrinsics when it is using the LLVM backend (as a matter of fact, Mono added these to LLVM for their own use).\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
