    "updated_at": "2013-06-19T21:01:44Z",
    "body": "This came up at lunch today. I'm led to understand that LLVM has a \"check if the last operation overflowed\" operation, so we should have a corresponding way (primitive or library) to check for it. Sometimes programmers want their operations to overflow (hashing), and sometimes not (pointer arithmetic) --we should leave that decision to them.\n",
